1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 (4. Nc3?! { See Theme #2 for a reminder of why Nc3 is an inaccuracy here. }) 4... Nc6 5. c3 Qc7 6. Ne2 (6. Nf3 Bg4 { Bg4 is basically an automatic response to Nf3, which almost always leads to equality right away. }) (6. h3 e5 7. dxe5 Nxe5 8. Bc2 Nf6 9. Nf3 Nxf3+ 10. Qxf3 Bd6 11. O-O O-O { Balanced position. }) 6... Bg4 7. f3 (7. O-O Nf6 8. Qe1 e6 9. f3 Bh5 10. Qh4 Bg6) 7... Bd7 8. Bf4 e5 9. dxe5 Nxe5 { White's f3 push hinders his position. Now Black can take over on the dark squares with Qb6 or Bc5 in the near future. } *


